 Privacy Policy

Effective date: <set date>

Kahana Inc. (“Kahana”, “we”, “us”) provides the Kahana Oasis platform, an AI‑powered browser and workspace used by individuals and organizations to manage their online work. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, share, and protect personal information when you use Kahana Oasis, visit our websites, or otherwise interact with us.

If you have any questions, you can contact us at: <privacy@kahana.>\

1. Scope and Who This Policy Covers
This Privacy Policy applies when:

You use Kahana Oasis (web app, browser integrations, related services).

You visit our websites or landing pages.

You communicate with us (for example, via email, support tickets, or other channels).

It applies to:

Individual users and team members of our customers.

Website visitors and prospective customers.

This Policy does not apply to third‑party websites, services, or browser content you visit using Oasis; those are governed by the third party’s own terms and privacy policies.

2. Information We Collect
2.1 Information You Provide to Us
We may collect the following information when you interact with us:

Account and profile information

Name, email address, password (stored as a hash), organization name, role, and similar details when you create or manage an account.

Workspace and configuration data

Information about your workspaces, hubs, and configuration choices within Oasis (for example, workspace names, labels, and settings).

Support and communication data

Content of messages you send to us (support requests, feedback, emails, survey responses).

2.2 Information We Collect Automatically
When you use Oasis or our websites, we may automatically collect:

Device and usage information

Browser type, operating system, language, basic device identifiers, and approximate region.

Log data such as timestamps, feature usage, performance metrics, and error details.

Limited usage analytics

Privacy‑respecting analytics about how features are used (for example, which features are used and how often), designed to avoid collecting the contents of your browsing activity or workspaces unless strictly necessary for the service.

We design Oasis to minimize collection of sensitive content such as full URLs, page contents, or documents unless needed to provide a feature you actively use.

2.3 Information from Third Parties
We may receive information from:

Single sign‑on (SSO) or identity providers

For example, your name, email, and basic profile attributes if your organization uses SSO to log in.

Payment providers

Limited billing‑related information such as transaction identifiers and subscription status. We do not store full payment card numbers; those are handled by our payment processor.

Business partners and vendors

Information needed to enable integrations or joint offerings, consistent with this Policy.

3. How We Use Personal Information
We use personal information for the following purposes:

To provide and maintain Kahana Oasis

Authenticate users, operate the service, maintain workspaces, and deliver requested features.

To secure and protect the service

Detect and prevent fraud, abuse, and security incidents.

Monitor and improve the security, reliability, and performance of Oasis.

To improve and develop our products

Analyze aggregated or de‑identified usage patterns to understand which features are helpful and where to improve.

To communicate with you

Send service‑related communications (account notifications, security alerts, changes to policies).

Respond to support requests and other inquiries.

Send optional product updates and marketing messages, where permitted by law and your preferences.

To comply with legal and contractual obligations

Maintain records as required by law, contracts, and our own compliance programs (including SOC 2).

We do not sell personal information.

4. Legal Bases (If Required in Your Jurisdictions)
Where required by law (for example, in the EU/UK), we rely on one or more of the following legal bases:

Performance of a contract (providing the service you subscribed to).

Legitimate interests (improving and securing our services, communicating with you about them).

Compliance with legal obligations.

Your consent, where we rely on consent (for example, certain marketing communications, cookies where required).

5. How We Share Information
We share information only as needed and with appropriate protections:

Service providers and sub‑processors

Trusted vendors who help us operate Kahana Oasis, such as cloud infrastructure providers, authentication/SSO providers, monitoring/analytics services, support tools, and payment processors.

These providers may access personal information only to perform services on our behalf and are bound by contractual confidentiality and security obligations.

Your organization (for business accounts)

If you use Kahana through an organization (e.g., your employer), administrators may have access to certain information about your account and usage consistent with that organization’s policies.

Business transfers

If we are involved in a merger, acquisition, financing, or sale of all or part of our business, personal information may be transferred as part of that transaction, subject to this Policy or a successor policy that provides at least similar protections.

Legal and safety reasons

Where required by law, subpoena, or legal process.

To protect the rights, property, or safety of Kahana, our users, or others.

We do not share your personal information with third parties for their independent marketing purposes without your consent.

6. Data Retention
We retain personal information only for as long as needed to:

Provide Kahana Oasis and related services.

Fulfill the purposes described in this Policy.

Comply with legal, tax, or accounting requirements.

At a high level:

Account and workspace data is retained while your account is active, and for a limited period afterward (for example, to support account reactivation or legal obligations), then deleted or anonymized consistent with our Data Retention and Destruction Policy.

Logs and security records are retained for a defined period to support security monitoring and incident response, then deleted or aggregated.

If you close your account, we will take steps to delete or anonymize personal data we no longer need, subject to legal or contractual retention requirements.

7. Data Security
We use appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect personal information, including:

Encryption of data in transit and at rest where appropriate.

Access controls based on least privilege and role‑based access.

Endpoint, network, and application security controls.

Logging and monitoring of security‑relevant events.

Regular backups and tested restoration procedures.

Security awareness training for employees.

No method of transmission or storage is 100% secure, but we work continuously to improve our security posture and align with industry standards and frameworks such as SOC 2.

8. International Transfers
Kahana may process and store information in countries other than where you live. Where we transfer personal information across borders, we do so:

Only when necessary to provide the service; and

Using appropriate safeguards as required by law (for example, standard contractual clauses or similar mechanisms, where applicable).

Your use of Kahana Oasis may involve such transfers; if you require more details, please contact us.

9. Your Rights and Choices
Depending on your location and applicable law, you may have rights such as:

Accessing the personal information we hold about you.

Requesting correction of inaccurate or incomplete data.

Requesting deletion of your personal information (subject to legal and operational limitations).

Objecting to or restricting certain processing.

Exporting your data in a portable format, where technically feasible.

You can exercise many of these rights through account settings; for others, you can contact us at <privacy email>. We will respond to lawful requests within a reasonable time and in accordance with applicable laws.

If we process your information based on consent, you may withdraw that consent at any time, though this will not affect processing already performed.

10. Children’s Privacy
Kahana Oasis is not directed to children under 16, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 16. If you believe a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us so we can take appropriate action.

11. Cookies and Similar Technologies
We may use cookies and similar technologies to:

Keep you signed in and maintain sessions.

Remember preferences.

Measure usage and improve the service.

Where required by law, we will obtain consent or provide options to manage cookie preferences. You can also control cookies through your browser settings, but some features may not work correctly if cookies are disabled.

12. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we make material changes, we will:

Update the “Effective date” above; and

Provide additional notice where appropriate (for example, by email or in‑app notice).

Your continued use of Kahana Oasis after any changes become effective constitutes your acceptance of the updated Policy.

